    {
      "id": "VXCdqvMQsnrI96ABpP1Ek",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1754.7777173760878,
      "y": 7934.100555865807,
      "width": 2151.00537109375,
      "height": 1390.509712837837,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#d0bfff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bE7",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 899983299,
      "version": 222,
      "versionNonce": 1011715901,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770053818754,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\n\n| Moment            | Question answered              | Class       |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------ | ----------- |\n| Vehicle enters    | “Where did you park & when?”   | **Ticket**  |\n| Vehicle exits     | “How much do you owe?”         | **Invoice** |\n| Money transaction | “Did money move successfully?” | **Payment** |\n\nUNIVERSAL RULE (use everywhere) 🔑\n\nWhenever you design LLD with payment:\nEVENT → FACT → CALCULATION → TRANSACTION\n\n| Layer       | Class   |\n| ----------- | ------- |\n| FACT        | Ticket  |\n| CALCULATION | Invoice |\n| TRANSACTION | Payment |\n\n\nWorks for:\n\nParking Lot\nMovie Booking\nHotel Booking\nEcommerce\nSubscription Billing\n\n“Ticket captures parking facts, Invoice calculates the payable amount, and Payment represents money movement.\nSeparating them allows retries, audits, refunds, and clean state transitions.”\n",
      "fontSize": 35.8841216216216,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\n\n| Moment            | Question answered              | Class       |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------ | ----------- |\n| Vehicle enters    | “Where did you park & when?”   | **Ticket**  |\n| Vehicle exits     | “How much do you owe?”         | **Invoice** |\n| Money transaction | “Did money move successfully?” | **Payment** |\n\nUNIVERSAL RULE (use everywhere) 🔑\n\nWhenever you design LLD with payment:\nEVENT → FACT → CALCULATION → TRANSACTION\n\n| Layer       | Class   |\n| ----------- | ------- |\n| FACT        | Ticket  |\n| CALCULATION | Invoice |\n| TRANSACTION | Payment |\n\n\nWorks for:\n\nParking Lot\nMovie Booking\nHotel Booking\nEcommerce\nSubscription Billing\n\n“Ticket captures parking facts, Invoice calculates the payable amount, and Payment represents money movement.\nSeparating them allows retries, audits, refunds, and clean state transitions.”\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
